Events.Text:
<i>Pretty much everyone loves the coast.░ Clear blue skies above the crystal clear waters of the shoreline:░ what's not to like, right?░
That's my town in a nutshell.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Don't get me wrong,░ this is the place to be if you want slim girls,░ hunky guys and curious tourists on the spectrum between those two.░ It's a hotspot holiday destination for anyone wanting to pay for the tranquility of an ocean breeze,░ with the occasional slap on the ass.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>It does wear thin,░ when this is all you have ever known.░ The beach gets gradually less interesting the more you see it.░ The constant barrage of skimpy trunks,░ lacy bikinis and a culture that embraces its liberal sexuality.░ I suppose I can see why it's such a big deal for outsiders,░ maybe I'm a little spoiled.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>I guess I'm just a bit of a stick in the mud.░ School and work always got in the way, you know?░ Anyway,░ there's more to life than trying to hook up with everyone in your senior year.░
I never really found the time to date after graduation,░ drifting apart from friends who had a different mindset.░ I see enough of that at home from my libido-driven brother.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
Neugh... 
<i>The sweet serenade of the alarm going off░, again.░ Time to get up and face reality.░ I'm beginning to wonder why I keep setting it in the first place...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>It feels like every morning I sleep past my wake up call a little longer.░ I guess it's pretty easy when there's nowhere you're expected to be in an hour.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>11am.░ At least I can still consider it 'breakfast' if I get up now.░ My motivation seems like it's extra low this week:░ saturday morning and it feels like the middle of the week still.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>Oh wait,░ I just remembered!░ Coby invited his friends over today...
Watching them get all touchy-feely gets kinda weird,░ considering we still share a bedroom.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Yeah, screw that░, I'm not going to pretend to sleep while they swap saliva.░ At least he's over at their place most of the time░, if I'm quick, I can dodge a bullet and sneak out the house before having to say hi.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>So far so good░, no sound of anyone while I was in the kitchen.░ I can grab a shower when I get back░, though I guess I still didn't work out where I'm going after the escape plan.░ I may as well decide on that now...
Events.Title: %playername%

Choices.Text: Get cleaned up and hand out more resumes.
Put on sneakers and go for a jog.
Go for a drive and see if there's anything fun in town.
Help out around the house.
Relax, chill out and use the internet.

Events.Text: <i>If I haven't been called by now, they probably aren't gonna call back.░ I may as well hit up as many places as possible░, at least then I'll have more of a case when Dad starts giving me that look again.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I only have my original copy left though,░ I'm gonna need to head down to the post office and print some copies.░ I should go take that shower now so I can look the part when I walk into these places, I wanna try to make the right impression at least.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hey, there's my ray of sunshine,░ you're looking chipper this morning!
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: Dammit Coby,░ gimme a heart attack why don't you?!░ I didn't even know you were home already!░ Where the hell are your clothes?░ Don't tell me you and your boyfriend are already doing it in my bedroom.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hey... That's not very nice, can't a little brother say good morning?░ Anyway, it's our bedroom don't forget!░ Just 'cause you're in there all the time doesn't mean it's yours all day!
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: Yeah, I guess I get that part,░ but the only time I see you in there is when you're getting bonked by some dude you just met.░ Excuse me for being a little bitter:░ especially when I'm trying to sleep and all I can hear is bed squeaks and bird squawks.░
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
For your information,░ it's just you and me at home.░
That's why I'm just in underwear!░ Don't you ever walk around the house naked when you know no one's watching?
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: You do it even when I'm around to see Cobes...
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Anyway, yeah... my friend?░ He isn't here.
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: When's he getting here then?░ I just wanna know how long I have the bathroom to myself before you're being thrown up against the glass.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
He isn't coming at all.░ 
He dumped me this morning,░ via text.
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: Woah,░ that's awful man.░ What a jerk way to do it!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I was wondering,░ can I spend the day with you?░ To cheer up I mean.
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: He seemed like a nice guy from when I met him, sorry Coby.░ You want to hang out?░ Let me think for a sec,░ you caught me right when I was going to do something.░
Events.Title: %playername%

Choices.Text: Make time for Coby.
Keep previous plans.

Events.Text: Hey cheer up ok?░ We'll go do something fun together and you can put that douchebag behind you.░ Well not behind you but...░ well you know what I'm trying to say.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: I knew I could count on you!░ You're always there for me.░ We hardly spend time together these days anyway!
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: Well you're hardly home.░ When you're not working,░ you're crashing at a friend's place.░ Probably up to no good as usual.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: If you wanted me around more,░ you coulda just told me!░ Remember when we used to share a queen-size bed together?░ You couldn't sleep unless I cuddled up next to you!
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: C'mon that was years ago!░ Plus it'd be weird now,░ we aren't kids anymore.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
Doesn't exactly change much to me!░ Speaking of sharing beds,░ is there anyone you've been bringing home?░ Are they cute?░ You certainly seem tired out when I get home!░
What?░ I'm just saying!
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: Don't tease,░ you know I haven't seen anyone in that way since high school.░ Even then I never really took my relationships seriously.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: You don't have to take them seriously to have fun and enjoy yourself!░ Not getting frisky is probably why you've been so mopey lately!
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: It's not that.░ It's just,░ not working for a few weeks kinda gets me down is all.░ I'm gonna have to sell some things soon to afford rent.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Should have told me you were feeling down!░ Hey don't worry about that stuff this week ok?░ I'll cover the rent this week for spending time with me!
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text: The way you say that makes me sound like a jerk who needs to be compensated for spend time with my step-brother.░ I love you Cobes,░  it's just seeing you with boyfriends all the time while I can't seem to find anyone for myself gets a little frustrating.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: Hey it's no sweat off my back!░ You covered my butt plenty of times when you were working.░ It's a shame you got laid off though.░ You seemed like you were good at that one!░
Events.Title: Coby

Events.Text:
No I love it when you're here,░ it's just...░ 
Well,░ I see you:░ you've finished school,░ you're out the house most of the time,░ working and loving life,░ exploring your sexuality;░ and here I am, I'm back at square one.░ 
Ha, I was wondering if I should bathe today.░ Big decisions.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
Aww,░ you're too sweet!░
You're not that far behind, you just need a kickstart and you'll be back on track!░ I can't really help you with the job hunting,░ but how about you and me go into town tonight and check out the clubs?░ I could use a fresh start myself,░ especially after this morning.
Events.Title: Coby

Choices.Text: Sure.
Do something else.

Events.Text: Well I did say I would spend the day with you,░ what harm could it do?░ If it gets boring we'll go to the movies or do something else instead.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>It was the first time myself and Coby had a dedicated day to each other for as long as I could remember.░ We seemed to have become distant during high school and it had kind of stuck that way ever since.░ 
Maybe this club thing wouldn't be so bad after all.░ I hadn't even thought about meeting people outside of work or school for a while.

Events.Text: <i>I put on an easy 2-player game that we could both play together.░ He loved platformers, but wasn't very good at them.░ On the other hand, he could whoop me easily in most fighting games...

Events.Text:
<i>It wasn't long until he convinced me to throw on competitive games.░ We started up a recent shooter,░ giving him a gentle nudge in the ribs every time I caught him spying on my side of the screen.░
He was better at those games,░ almost winning as much as I did.░ I was glad that our parents were out when it turned to playful verbal abuse.

Events.Text: <i>We had just enough time to squeeze in a few rounds at his favourite fighting game.░ I have no idea when he became so good at them░ but, no matter what character he picked, he seemed to know what he was doing far better than me.░ He was actually using his special moves in combos,░ I was stuck spamming the moves I knew randomly and hoping for the best.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>He gave me a big hug before pointing out the time.░ If we wanted to go out tonight, we had to get ready soon...

I'm sure I can dress myself...░
Go get cleaned up,░ we should get going soon!

Events.Text: <i>Alright,░ knowing Coby,░ he's gonna be in there for ages.░ I'll have plenty of time to get ready.░ Now it's just a matter of figuring out where to start!

Maybe this club thing wouldn't be so bad after all.░ I hadn't even thought about meeting people outside of work or school for a while.

Events.Text: <i>He peered over my shoulder as we scanned the shelves of the pantry and fridge.░ I just wanted to make some simple hotdogs but he insisted we make something we could work on together.

Events.Text: <i>He always loved playing with flour,░ flattening the dough and getting it all over the place.░ He offered for me to taste his batter but I had to turn it down.░ Unrisen pizza dough isn't really the same as cake batter when it's still on the spoon.

Events.Text:
<i>We helped each other clean up while we waited for it to bake in the oven.░ He still somehow managed to sit on the counter and get flour all over his butt in the process...░
Not that he'd ever seemed to mind getting flogged with a dish towel.░

Maybe this club thing wouldn't be so bad after all.░ I hadn't even thought about meeting people outside of work or school for a while.

Events.Text: <i>We didn't have many movies in the living room to pick from.░ I presented him with a few old DVDs and he picked one of the movies we watched when we were younger.░ I wasn't big on animated movies these days but I still was happy to watch it with him.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>We both had a few laughs over the course of the film.░ Even though it was fairly old,░ it still held up pretty well.░ It had been long enough ago that some parts of the movie felt new to me.░ Coby was getting all hyper once it was over and started wrestling with me,░ ever the kid at heart even if we were practically the same age.░ I put on another movie so we didn't wreck the livingroom entirely.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>This one was released this year.░ It had a used sticker still on the cover but neither of us had seen it.░ It was very much a popcorn movie,░ lots of action and big scenes of drama.░ Coby had calm down,░ cuddling up to my side over the later half.░ I didn't mind, it was nice to snuggle up with him.░ Like he said, we'd done it all the time when we were younger.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>We both took a big breath as the screen went black and the credits began to roll.░ Another one of those twist endings that is meant to leave you in awe.░
We burnt away the rest of the afternoon theorizing about the obvious sequel bait,░ it was a fun time.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I let him disappear into the bedroom while I threw on my sneakers.░ As I looked for the house keys to lock up, I had to sigh as he returned.░ He had successfully put on his shoes,░ but was still only wearing his underwear otherwise.░ I ordered him to march back into the bedroom and put his clothes on.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>As much as I love my brother,░ I didn't want to be seen with him almost nude, skipping down the street.░ I suppose it was encouraging that he had never had a problem with his body,░ as much as his blue booty frequently found an excuse to be on display.░
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>The thuds were usually a good indicator that he was in the middle of doing things with his boyfriend when he needed to answer the door,░ I guess not today, poor guy...░ 
When he was finally ready, we headed out.░ It was a cloudless day,░ a little hot, but nothing to break a sweat over.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>The walk into town wasn't too long,░ we both picked up a soda for ourselves while we roamed past some stores,░ having to drag Coby along every time he wanted to stop and browse for too long.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>It was refreshing to do something simple for once.░ We both recalled biking around the town when we were younger and the town center seemed like an endless playground.░ How we used to play in the town's park,░ bringing up familiar names of school friends and those old adventures was nice.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>We got lost in conversation for quite a while before realizing the time.░ If we wanted to go out tonight, we had to get ready soon...

Events.Text:
<i>We had an old rule between us:░ when we had no guests in the house, the bedroom was an underwear only zone.░
Considering it was just us, I didn't really think too much of it.░ He wasn't the type to pull pranks while we were almost naked.░ He made a fair argument that he was already in his, and I had to get cleaned up soon anyway if we were going to go out.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Being mature as always, he began whistling while I undressed.░ Sometimes I think he made the rule just to get a kick out of me stripping.░ He had a really wide range of whistles too,░ I guess that's an avian thing to sing and whistle really well?░ It's fun just waiting to hear what he'd come up with next when I'm changing,░ even if it did make me feel a little like I was performing for an audience.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I tried to convince him to use the computer with me, but the chance to play on the bed was too tantalizing for him to turn down.░ We initially laid side by side,░ staring at the roof with our arms folded behind our heads.░ Just chilling in our briefs, talking about anything that came to mind.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>I never thought of Coby being the type,░ but he knows a fair bit of trivia should he ever get the opportunity to share it.░ Not just movies and games either,░ I guess he payed more attention in school than I thought.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text:
<i>Sure enough, being my brother, we ended up wrestling once we started getting restless.░ He's deceptively strong for his size.░ Pinning my arms down and getting atop me more than once before I threw him off me and did the same.░
Not exactly a thing to read too far into, ░even if this kind of wrestling meant something different if it was someone else in here with him.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>We eventually called a truce and laid our limbs over each other in an exhausted pile.░ If we wanted to go out tonight, we had to get ready soon...

<i>I'm not gonna accomplish anything when I'm content to be lazy at home.░ Keeping fit is gonna give me my energy back!░ 
I might actually start waking up before the sun starts to go down.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>It's probably being stuck at home that's making me all philosophical in the mornings.░ Some fresh air will do me wonders!
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>It's a bit of an odd hour to catch a movie, all the good flicks are on in the evening.░ I could always grab a towel and head down to the gym or the beach.░ It's a beautiful day either way░, it'd suck to waste it inside.

Events.Text: <i>I don't think mom or Dad are home.░ I would have been woken up far earlier if that were the case.░ If not by Dad himself, it'd be the two of them crashing around the kitchen and living room doing the weekly cleaning.

Events.Text: <i>I decided to let Coby drive since he knew the way.░ He was such a regular, and had dated one of the bouncers briefly,░ that we didn't have to worry about waiting in line when we got there.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: It was one of those clubs.░ Once the staff knew you, you were fine░, otherwise you had to be very patient to even see the inside.░ We drove through the illuminated side of town,░ the sun now well on its way to setting,░ nightlife bustling all around us from the bars and waterfront restaurants.
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>Coby kept reassuring me that I'd have a blast░, I think he could read my nerves pretty easily.░ I'd gotten myself into this without really thinking it through:░ what if the club filled with the type of guys Coby liked to date?░ He's not always the best judge of character,░ he can be way too nice to everyone and I'm certainly a bit more picky.

Events.Text:
<i>I suppose, technically, Coby had his long distance boyfriend to anchor him these days,░ but he wasn't exactly looking to head home empty-handed.░ His boyfriend knew what a free spirit he was░, and they had some sort of agreement whilst they were apart.░ Coby always seemed to find someone who'd take advantage of his carefree attitude though.░
On the flip side,░ I should probably try to be more adventurous if I didn't want to spend all my time trying to block out the sound of Coby having fun with his local boyfriends.░
Events.Title: %playername%

Events.Text: <i>It was refreshing to step outside,░ the bouncer gave us a gentle wave,░ sharpie in hand as he addressed the next in line.

Events.Text: <i>I felt a little bad for pressuring Coby to leave earlier than he usually would have,░ but he was all smiles.░ He was just happy that I came, I suppose.
